parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Line Failure due to Improper Assembly
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake line can cause a loss of braking pressure, leading to increased stopping distances, accidents, and potentially life-threatening situations.
symptoms: brake pedal goes to the floor
worn groove in the brake line

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear ABS brakes can cause the wheels to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially life-threatening situations.
Rust-related brake system failure can cause a loss of braking pressure, leading to increased stopping distances, accidents, and potentially life-threatening situations.
Warped rotors can cause vibration, noise, and reduced braking performance, leading to increased stopping distances and potentially life-threatening situations.
Severe rust perforation in the frame of the vehicle can cause structural failure, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: separation of the front axle bracket from the frame

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the door handles can cause inconvenience, difficulty in entering or exiting the vehicle, and potentially lead to accidents or injuries if the door opens unexpectedly while the vehicle is in motion.
The failure of the engine head gasket can cause engine knocking, stalling, and eventual engine failure, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.

The engine knocking or tapping noise can be a sign of engine head gasket failure, piston ring failure, or other engine component failure, which can lead to engine damage and eventual failure, increasing the risk of accidents.
Intermittent engine stalling can cause a loss of power and control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
The failure of the power mirror can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The passenger side power mirror is inoperative

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fan blower motor can cause discomfort, distraction, and reduced visibility due to fog or mist, increasing the risk of accidents.
The failure of the rearview mirror can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
The delamination and cracking of the tire sidewalls can lead to a loss of tire pressure, reduced traction, and increased risk of tire failure, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Visible peeling or delamination of the tire sidewalls
and enormous cracks in the tread section of the tires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation of the tire tread can cause damage to the wheel well and body, and can lead to a loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: damage to the wheel well and body
and retention of full air pressure despite the damage.
